post_text:
We are excited that our fall sports contests begin this week. However, we are taking many precautions to protect our student-athletes, participants, coaches and spectators.

The spectator experience and ticket purchasing process will be different this year:

- Each person participating in a sports contest, including athletes, band, etc., will be allowed four tickets per game;
- The participant must give the names of the four people they want to attend the game to the school in the days prior to the game;
- Only spectators on that list will be permitted access to the game.

For ticket purchasing information - please check out HillsboroughSchools.org/athletics - which also includes a list of frequently asked questions.

